stylometry: Data mining is taking raw data and putting it in a information warehouse and from there finding trends in  the data. This is very important to companys becuase trend analysis can help predict future occurances, and they can hopefully capitalize on these trends. To do this we use cluseter analysis. To do this you take the raw data and divide it into different demographic groups, for example you can cluster a whole division of lacrosse teams statistics by making their team names the index for your model, then taking the statistics for that team such as saves, assists and goals for their season and putting them next to the idex. From there you take the averages of each statistic you want to look at which would be saves assists and goals.Then you can find the best three teams with the best similar statistics. From there you can take the averages of those three teams and compare the rest of the division statistics and group the teams under one of the top three teams that have similar statistics. You then can see which teams will have the best competition due to similar statistics. Data mining basically gives us a detailed overview of the data provided and abstracts averages from the data, which can be used to cluster the data into groups of similar behavior. Why this is important in business is because if a company would produce a survey for their product and take the information from that survery and cluster the group of people that are more likely to buy that product then they can manufactor their product to those specific locations where consumer awearness was high and cosumers were willing to purchase their product. Instead of just randomly choosing a location and hoping for the best for their product. A company can get a more accurate location on where to sell their product.
